title.narrative: Caribbean Geothermal Technical Assistance Phase II Activity

description.narrative: The Caribbean Geothermal Technical Assistance (CGTA) activity is a flexible, demand-driven Technical Assistance (TA) facility supporting the development of geothermal energy across Eastern Caribbean Island states. Phase I of this support ($NZ$5.6m 2014-2018) is in completion. Phase II will invest NZ$5.1m in an extended period of support over 2018-2021.
